cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.SI 

The paper discusses a routing protocol for multi-channel cognitive radio networks, which involves network coding and opportunistic routing. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper also discusses the impact of primary user behavior on spectrum availability, which is related to cognitive radio (cs.CR). The use of network coding also involves multimedia communication (cs.MM) and the proposed protocol considers multiple factors to optimize performance, which is related to systems and control (cs.SI).
